tonight?

03:46.527 --> 03:50.462
I talked to her this morning.

03:50.464 --> 03:53.298
She and I talked,

03:53.300 --> 03:57.302
and she said
she might go to the movies,

03:57.304 --> 04:00.672
and I told her not to walk.

04:00.674 --> 04:02.407
The movie,

04:02.409 --> 04:04.376
Mr. Ryder--

04:04.378 --> 04:07.446
would you know which one
that would be?

04:07.448 --> 04:09.715
She likes the 69th Street Twin.

04:09.717 --> 04:11.750
Mr. Ryder, do you
happen to have

04:11.752 --> 04:14.386
a photo of her
that we could borrow?

04:14.388 --> 04:16.788
Daddy...

04:17.858 --> 04:20.759
Daddy, is something wrong?

04:25.499 --> 04:27.799
Where's Mommy?

04:30.437 --> 04:33.739
MAN:
<i> Scandinavian film festival?</i>

04:33.741 --> 04:35.607
People committing suicide
in the snow.

04:35.609 --> 04:38.744
Not exactly what New Yorkers
want to see in the winter.

04:38.746 --> 04:41.546
We sold 86 tickets.

04:41.548 --> 04:43.849
One to her?

04:43.851 --> 04:49.354
I'm so bored I'm working
with my eyes closed.

04:49.356 --> 04:51.423
Okay, thanks.

04:54.428 --> 04:57.429
Six more bars,
four Korean fruit stands.

04:57.431 --> 04:58.830
Nobody saw her.

04:58.832 --> 05:00.432
What's he got?

05:00.434 --> 05:02.367
Suicide.

05:02.369 --> 05:04.369
In Swedish.

05:04.371 --> 05:06.872
DOCTOR:
<i> Massive blunt-force trauma--</i>

05:06.874 --> 05:09.641
matches the other victims--
this guy is batting a thousand.

05:09.643 --> 05:11.877
She ate an hour before
she died-- meat, huh?

05:11.879 --> 05:13.512
Maybe she found
an art house

05:13.514 --> 05:15.480
that served carpaccio
with her cappuccino.

05:15.482 --> 05:17.749
Hey, you find semen
in the vagina, you
don't call us?

05:17.751 --> 05:20.419
Nobody said it was rape--
there's no sign of rape:

05:20.421 --> 05:21.920
no tearing, no abrasions...

05:21.922 --> 05:23.655
Her husband was out of town.

05:23.657 --> 05:25.390
to know that?
I'm supposed

05:25.392 --> 05:27.459
What am I, his travel agent?

05:27.460 --> 05:29.527
What time
did she do it?
Before midnight last night--

05:29.530 --> 05:32.147
sperm cells were dead
this morning.

05:32.148 --> 05:34.765
And after midnight Friday--
I found acid phosphatase,
seminal fluid.

05:34.768 --> 05:37.469
Disappears 48 hours
after intercourse.

05:37.471 --> 05:40.505
Of course, it's also found
in cauliflower juice.

05:40.507 --> 05:44.443
Oh, I think we can
rule out a cauliflower.

05:44.445 --> 05:45.811
Your friend Saperstein
from the three-six?

05:45.813 --> 05:48.613
Jewelry from one
of the other murders

05:48.615 --> 05:51.883
turned up in the diamond
district-- not traceable.

05:51.885 --> 05:55.787
Why does she go to a late movie
with two little kids at home?

05:55.789 --> 05:57.656
Maybe because she<i> had</i>
two little kids at home.

05:57.658 --> 05:58.790
And because she has
a housekeeper.

05:58.792 --> 06:01.493
She's not going
to tell the housekeeper

06:01.495 --> 06:02.861
where she's going?

06:02.863 --> 06:04.529
She had dinner,
she had sex.

06:04.531 --> 06:05.764
Spells boyfriend.

06:05.766 --> 06:07.532
Maybe a lovers' quarrel?

06:07.534 --> 06:09.968
Or the husband wasn't gone
for four days.

06:09.970 --> 06:12.871
Well, it would be nice to know
who she was sleeping with.

06:12.873 --> 06:14.806
You're gonna have
to go see the husband.

06:14.808 --> 06:16.808
Boy, if it wasn't him

06:16.810 --> 06:21.046
this is a lousy time
to bring him that kind of news.

06:21.048 --> 06:22.981
My son's under sedation.

06:22.983 --> 06:24.816
This is not a good time.

06:24.818 --> 06:27.552
We really do have
to talk to him.

06:27.554 --> 06:29.988
The children, the
funeral arrangements...

06:29.990 --> 06:31.857
he's very upset.

06:31.859 --> 06:33.592
Mr. Ryder,
sorry to bother you.

06:33.594 --> 06:35.761
If we could just
have a minute privately.

06:35.763 --> 06:38.530
The family
is in this together.

06:38.532 --> 06:41.500
CERRETA:
I really
don't think...

06:41.502 --> 06:43.502
No.

06:43.504 --> 06:45.470
We'll talk.

06:45.472 --> 06:47.873
Your wife--
there's medical evidence

06:47.875 --> 06:50.509
that indicates that she had
intimate relations

06:50.511 --> 06:52.677
in the 48 hours
before she died.

06:52.679 --> 06:55.046
Well, that's impossible.
Um...

06:55.048 --> 06:58.583
I went to Southampton
on Thursday.

06:58.585 --> 07:01.920
Well, if it wasn't you...

07:01.922 --> 07:04.055
What are you saying?

07:04.057 --> 07:07.526
My wife was having an affair?

07:07.528 --> 07:09.494
I'm sure Lois

07:09.496 --> 07:11.863
was doing no such thing.

07:11.865 --> 07:13.031
If we could track
her movements

07:13.033 --> 07:15.567
we might find a witness
to her murder.

07:15.569 --> 07:17.135
It can't be.

07:17.137 --> 07:20.071
I know my wife.
It's possible
the lab was wrong.

07:20.073 --> 07:23.008
If you would just
take a blood test,
we'd know it's you,

07:23.010 --> 07:25.510
We don't have to look for
someone that doesn't exist.

07:25.512 --> 07:27.045
My daughter-in-law
is dead,

07:27.047 --> 07:29.714
my grandchildren
don't have a mother,

07:29.716 --> 07:33.585
and you want to drag my son
through some cheap scandal.

07:36.023 --> 07:38.790
I don't think so. No.

07:38.792 --> 07:41.159
LOGAN:
<i> So, you tell me,</i>
<i> what's the big deal</i>

07:41.161 --> 07:42.761
about taking
a blood test?

07:42.763 --> 07:44.029
Your wife just died.

07:44.031 --> 07:45.897
Maybe you don't
like being asked

07:45.899 --> 07:48.133
to prove that she
wasn't sleeping around.

07:48.135 --> 07:50.836
Maybe he didn't want us to know
he saw her over the weekend.

07:50.838 --> 07:52.571
Your guy Ryder--
draft bait Vietnam.

07:52.573 --> 07:54.573
Joined the National Guard,
Dan Quayle Brigade.

07:54.575 --> 07:56.575
The army found
his DD-214.

07:56.577 --> 07:57.776
Blood type "A."

07:57.778 --> 07:59.578
Doesn't match the semen.

07:59.580 --> 08:01.713
So why won't he take the test?

08:01.715 --> 08:04.333
Like I said--

08:04.334 --> 08:06.952
grieving husband, privacy,
maybe he just don't like cops.

08:06.954 --> 08:08.753
wouldn't match.
Maybe he knew it

08:08.755 --> 08:10.789
Didn't want us to know
she had a boyfriend

08:10.791 --> 08:12.123
and that he had a motive.

08:12.125 --> 08:14.793
I'll tell you one person
who saw her before she died--

08:14.795 --> 08:16.761
the boyfriend.

08:16.763 --> 08:18.063
Where do you have her last?

08:18.065 --> 08:20.799
The housekeeper says
the hospital--

08:20.801 --> 08:22.868
Carnegie Hill,
volunteer work.

08:22.870 --> 08:24.703
What are you waiting for?

08:24.705 --> 08:27.105
I need people
to hold patients' hands.

08:27.107 --> 08:30.075
Most volunteers, they want
to work the resale shop

08:30.077 --> 08:32.944
on Madison--
first dibs on the used Adolfos.

08:32.946 --> 08:35.113
So you didn't know
Mrs. Ryder well?

08:35.115 --> 08:36.848
Ryder money built
this hospital.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.650
Lois should've been part
of that crowd,

08:38.652 --> 08:40.051
but she didn't understand
the game.

08:40.053 --> 08:42.821
Worked the pediatric
cancer ward.

08:42.823 --> 08:46.024
Did she ever tell you
about her life?

08:46.026 --> 08:48.760
LOGAN:
We think she had

08:48.762 --> 08:50.195
a boyfriend.

08:52.032 --> 08:53.765
I wouldn't know.

08:53.767 --> 08:56.034
CERRETA:
Miss Phillips...

08:56.036 --> 08:58.837
you can either tell<i> us</i>
or a grand jury.

08:58.839 --> 08:59.971
He's married.

08:59.973 --> 09:01.106
He has kids.

09:01.108 --> 09:02.908
Leave him out of it.

09:02.910 --> 09:04.175
He's already in it.

09:04.177 --> 09:06.177
What's his name?

09:09.149 --> 09:12.684
Joel Friedman,
chief of pediatrics.

09:15.756 --> 09:17.122
Lois Ryder.

09:17.124 --> 09:19.124
Of course I knew her.

09:19.126 --> 09:22.027
She volunteered
at the hospital.

09:22.029 --> 09:24.896
Were you with her
Sunday night?

09:24.898 --> 09:27.766
I don't know
what you're talking about.

09:27.768 --> 09:29.968
We'll make it easy
for you.

09:29.970 --> 09:32.137
Sunday night,
Lois Ryder,

09:32.139 --> 09:34.773
you, together.

09:34.775 --> 09:38.743
Do you want us
to tell you
your rights?

09:38.745 --> 09:40.812
Who is it, honey?

09:43.016 --> 09:45.150
Uh, I'll get my coat.

09:45.152 --> 09:48.219
CERRETA:
<i> We want a blood test.</i>

09:48.221 --> 09:51.056
And if you're not going
to give it to us

09:51.058 --> 09:52.924
we'll get a court order.
Relax, gentlemen.

09:52.926 --> 09:54.993
Joel.

10:00.767 --> 10:04.035
I was with her.

10:04.037 --> 10:07.072
We'd been seeing
each other

10:07.074 --> 10:09.774
about five months.

10:09.776 --> 10:12.043
Normally, I...

10:12.045 --> 10:14.779
I wouldn't see her
at my apartment.

10:14.781 --> 10:16.281
She called.

10:16.283 --> 10:18.049
She wanted to talk.

10:18.051 --> 10:19.985
CERRETA:
Her husband says

10:19.987 --> 10:22.053
they were happily married.

10:22.055 --> 10:24.322
Really?

10:29.062 --> 10:31.162
No.

10:31.164 --> 10:34.933
No. There's a picture
in the Ryder house.

10:34.935 --> 10:37.902
Lois told me.

10:37.904 --> 10:41.172
His grandmother on a camel,
Egypt, 1930.

10:41.174 --> 10:44.075
In 1930, her grandmother
was scrubbing floors

10:44.077 --> 10:46.211
in East Orange, New Jersey,

10:46.213 --> 10:50.815
and the Ryders
never let her forget that.

10:50.817 --> 10:53.118
I can't be involved in this.

10:53.120 --> 10:57.022
Did her husband know
about the affair?

10:59.993 --> 11:04.029
I saw him last month
at a hospital fund-raiser.

11:04.031 --> 11:06.031
He smirked at me.

11:06.033 --> 11:07.832
He knew.

11:10.137 --> 11:14.272
Lois didn't understand
what she was doing.

11:14.274 --> 11:17.042
I did.

11:17.044 --> 11:20.045
I was there
to make him jealous.

11:20.047 --> 11:21.179
He's cooperating.

11:21.181 --> 11:23.214
He didn't kill her.

11:23.216 --> 11:26.051
I know it.
You know it.

11:33.894 --> 11:35.026
She's using him.

11:35.028 --> 11:36.895
Maybe he loses
his temper.

11:36.896 --> 11:38.763
The elevator man says
the doc's wife got home

11:38.765 --> 11:40.131
40 minutes after
Lois Ryder left.

11:40.133 --> 11:42.133
He was waiting
at the door for her.

11:42.135 --> 11:43.802
That gives him just
about enough time.

11:43.804 --> 11:45.270
Fire escape dumps
into a locked yard,

11:45.272 --> 11:47.806
