clobbers Lois Ryder,

11:49.276 --> 11:52.243
hauls her body from the west
side to the east side

11:52.245 --> 11:55.146
and gets home just in time
to kiss his wife hello?

11:55.148 --> 11:58.149
What is he, Houdini?
Yeah.

11:58.151 --> 12:02.120
The doc here says that
Ryder knew about him

12:02.122 --> 12:05.223
and Ryder said
he<i> didn't</i> know.

12:08.028 --> 12:09.260
I knew.

12:11.164 --> 12:17.102
I just didn't see why the rest
of the world had to know.

12:17.104 --> 12:19.638
<i> We</i> had to know.

12:19.639 --> 12:22.173
He was one of the last
people to see her alive.

12:22.175 --> 12:23.975
My granddaughter--

12:23.977 --> 12:26.177
should she read
in the newspaper

12:26.179 --> 12:28.179
about her mother's
infidelity?

12:28.181 --> 12:30.949
And especially
with someone so foreign.

12:30.951 --> 12:33.218
Yes. He's from the west side.

12:33.220 --> 12:36.221
You know what I mean--
he was not of our element.

12:36.223 --> 12:40.091
